SIMPLE: petite
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: petite
<hw>pe*tite"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., fem. of
<ets>petit</ets>.]</ety> <def>Small, little; -- used especially of a
woman or girl, of small size and trim figure; <as>as, her
<ex>petite</ex> figure</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bantam, diminutive, lilliputian, midget,
tiny.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>petite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: petite
<hw>pe*tite"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fem. of
<ets>petit</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A size category of women's
clothing, for women with less than average height.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An aricle of women's clothing classified in the
<er>petite</er>{1} size category.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A girl or woman whose figure is best fit by a
<er>petite</er>{1} garment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>petitio</ent>⟦br⟧
